wikipedia_page.main: Sarah Northey was a silver medalist in the ladies synchronized swimming event at the 1990 Commonwealth Games. Born in Taunton, Somerset, she later moved to Reading. Sarah is the youngest of three daughters by Colin and Jacqueline Northey.
